                                                    java.lang.String bandingStyle,
                                                    java.lang.String historicTrafficTimeBucket)
                                             throws ApiException
        Gets travel Boundary by Distance Returns the travel boundary based on travel distance.
        Parameters:
        costs - Travel distance(s) (required)
        point - Starting point from where the travel boundary is calculated. Point in 'Lat,Long,coordsys' format (optional)
        address - Starting address from where the travel boundary is calculated. (optional)
        costUnit - Travel distance such as ft(Foot), km(Kilometer), mi(Mile), m(Meter) or yd(Yard). (optional, default to m)
        db - Mode of commute. (optional, default to driving)
        country - Three digit ISO country code. (optional, default to USA)
        maxOffroadDistance - Maximum distance to allow travel off the road network. (optional)
        maxOffroadDistanceUnit - MaxOffroad Distance Unit such as ft(Foot), km(Kilometer), mi(Mile), m(Meter) or yd(Yard). (optional)
        destinationSrs - Desired coordinate system of the travel boundary. (optional)
        majorRoads - Whether to include all roads in the calculation or just major roads. (optional, default to false)
        returnHoles - Whether to return holes, which are areas within the larger boundary that cannot be reached within the desired distance. (optional, default to false)
        returnIslands - Whether to return islands, which are small areas outside the main boundary that can be reached within the desired distance. (optional, default to false)
        simplificationFactor - Number between 0.0 and 1.0 where 0.0 is very simple and 1.0 means the most complex. (optional, default to 0.5)
        bandingStyle - Style of banding to be used in the result. (optional, default to Donut)
        historicTrafficTimeBucket - Whether routing calculation uses the historic traffic speeds. (optional, default to None)
        Returns:
        TravelBoundaries
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
